New Silicon Valley
For many years, it was considered a secret city, inaccessible to Western visitors.
Selenograd, one of the ten districts of Moscow, was in the Soviet Union a heavily guarded site for secret weapons investigation.
Today, the community of 216,000 inhabitants, located 37 kilometres from central Moscow, is considered to be the "Russian Silicon Valley".
Here are important research and production centers for micro and nanoelectronics.
Since September 2008, Selenograd representatives have contacted Riedberg's scientific headquarters in Frankfurt, university institutes and companies at the Frankfurt Innovation Centre (FIZ).
Several mutual visits were made, and now, on Wednesday, Selenograd and Riedberg sign a "close collaboration protocol" in Frankfurt.
