In 2010 they will travel to a seminar in Selenograd representatives of the FIZ and directors of small and medium-sized enterprises at the Natural Sciences Research Centre.
Scientific exchange
This is a continuous scientific exchange.
But it also deals with commercial relations.
The FIZ companies will have the opportunity to set foot in the growing Russian market.
In exchange, Russian scientific companies want to have access to contracts in Germany.
Selenograd is home to important Russian companies and research institutes.
Among them are, for example, the Moscow Institute of Electronic Technology, the great Sitronics and Rossijskaja Elektronika consortia.
The community was founded in 1958 as the so-called "Socialist Planning City" for weapons research.
Selenograd (literally translated as "Green City") received its name from the landscape of forested mountains, in which research facilities were established.
