Aristotle conceived hallucinations as a form of sleep in the state of vigil, Wilhelm Griesinger, one of the founders of modern psychiatry, observed in 1861 a "great similarity of the state of madness with the states of onirics", for Sigmund Freud, the dream was even "a psychosis, with all the misappropriations, crazy formations, and speculations of it".
