According to Fuchs, states of emergency can lead anyone to lose contact with reality provisionally.
But not all people develop psychosis.
There seems to be a genetic disposition for schizophrenia, but twin studies have shown that in addition to genes there are also other determining factors.
Researchers assume that the affected suffer minimal brain damage.
