But it remains an unknown how this alteration of the neuronal system occurs, which also does not manifest itself at all for many years.
The influence of the environment also plays an important role – stress or traumatic experience can be the triggers of a psychosis when there is already a previous disposition.
Similarly, hallucinogenic drugs can cause psychosis as they interfere with the brain's transmitting system.
