Four-step workshop budget
With the Auda-Taller tool, the Audadex company ensures that the user gets a budget in just four steps: identify the vehicle, search for replacement, create budget and generate budget.
Ease of use is an essential condition for these systems, especially to convince older professionals, who to a greater or lesser extent are more reluctant to use new management techniques.
The database includes 1,034 vehicles, which are 666 passenger cars, 109 toasters, 137 motorcycles, 78 vans and 44 trucks.
Of course, a computer with internet connection is needed to use it.
Once the model is identified to be repaired using its frame number, a real graphic image of the model in question appears and then the necessary replacement is selected.
The user can include variables such as labor price, surcharges or discounts, and then you can print the budget to deliver to the customer.
AudaWorker is not a valuation tool like AudaPlus, but rather a catalogue of references.
The main difference between the two systems is that the workshop orientation does not include estimated labour times.
The cost of using this tool for the workshop is 350 euros per year, which the customer can finance.
